FBIS4-37467 "drnes119_l_94014" FBIS-NES-94-119 Daily Report 19 Jun 1994 ISRAEL Arms Embargo Against South Africa Officially Lifted Arms Embargo Against South Africa Officially Lifted MB1906164094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1600 GMT 19 Jun 94 MB1906164094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] Israel has become the first country to officially lift its arms embargo against South Africa. This follows the United Nations Security Council's resolution last month to cancel the military embargo and other restrictions it had imposed in the past. There had been speculation that the two countries were cooperating on nuclear weapons and ballistic missile research until Israel stopped signing arms contracts with South Africa in 1987.
